{"version": 2, "width": 100, "height": 30, "timestamp": 1764950400, "env": {"SHELL": "/bin/bash", "TERM": "xterm-256color"}, "title": "HELIX align: detect drift in the artifact graph"}
[0.0, "o", "\r\n\u001b[2m# A team has a HELIX-governed project. The PRD says auth is API-key only, but a recent ADR proposes OAuth. Time to run alignment.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.0, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;32m$ tree docs/helix -L 2\u001b[0m\r\n"]
